<br>
How many would be in favor of an improved Manaburn (Planar Manaburn maybe?) that required a comparable amount of AA points to achieve?  The old Manaburn would be a prerequisite, along with a considerable amount of other AAs with the same desirability as those the SKs must pick up to achieve IHT.<br>
<br>
What I want here is a useful Manaburn.  I'm willing to spend 100AA on it to get it if that is what it will take.<br>
<br>
I'm thinking of something along these lines:<br>
<br>
----------------<br>
Name: Planar Manaburn<br>
Pre-Requisite(s): Manaburn, Spell Casting Fury Mastery 3, Fury of Magic Mastery 3, Innate Enlightenment 5<br>
Level Requirement: 65<br>
Ability Type: Activated<br>
Max Training: 1 Levels<br>
Point Cost: 13 points<br>
Description: This ability allows the Wizard to deal the most powerful direct damage in the game, improving upon the old Manaburn.  It takes all of the Wizards remaining mana to deliver an enormous blast.  The damage done is greater than three times the mana used and can not be resisted.  The ability can be used once every 2 game days, but not more than once per minute on any single mob.<br>
------------<br>
<br>
I believe that's 65AA points to achieve it.<br>
<br>
-Raystonn<br>
