<br>
Oh and most PoP encounters don't involve a single target.  Lets take Xegony first.  She calls an army of adds as you attack her.  A boss in each army wields a fairly deadly AE.  Most of them have very low HP.  A manaburn blast of that size would mostly kill them, exposing your raid to the AE maybe once before its dead.  Wizards could take turns MBing each boss wave.  Being able to do so would drastically gimp the encounter.<br>
<br>
Corniav is a race against the clock.  There are 3 sub bosses that must die before you can attack Corniav.  Again wizards could take turns MBing each boss.  Then a fourth wizard could nuke Corniav.  Just to give you an idea I generally get two SoSes off before he dies.  6200ish dmg from me compared to 19500.  Yeah that wouldn't gimp the encounter!<br>
<br>
Then there is the Rathe.  12 NPCs, and a race against spawntime.  Well you get the picture.  Again each wizard could MB a different one.  Destroyed yet another encounter! <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~kosmos00/elysig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
